  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a medium-high heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>meat-free bacon lardons</strong> to the pan and cook for 4-5 min or until golden and crispy</p><p>Once crispy, transfer the <strong>cooked meat-free bacon lardons</strong> to a clean plate and set aside, reserve the pan</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-mushroom-leek-goats-cheese-linguine/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst the bacon is cooking, wash your <strong>leek[s]</strong> carefully to remove any grit from between the leaves, then top, tail and slice finely</p><p>Slice your<strong> chestnut mushrooms</strong> finely</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your<strong> garlic</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-mushroom-leek-goats-cheese-linguine/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your<strong> linguine</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> with a large pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the<strong> </strong>linguine for 8-10 min or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain the linguine, reserving a cup of the <strong>starchy pasta water</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-mushroom-leek-goats-cheese-linguine/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pan to a medium-high heat with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped mushrooms</strong> and <strong>sliced leek</strong> to the pan with a pinch of<strong> salt </strong>and cook for 5-7 min or until everything is beginning to soften</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-mushroom-leek-goats-cheese-linguine/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, grate your <strong>cheddar cheese</strong></p><p>Dissolve your<strong> vegetable stock mix</strong> in 100ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[150ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[200ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-mushroom-leek-goats-cheese-linguine/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the vegetables have softened, add the <strong>sliced garlic</strong> to the pan and cook for 1 min further or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>vegetable stock</strong> with a generous grind of <strong>black pepper</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-mushroom-leek-goats-cheese-linguine/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Remove the pan from the heat and add your <strong>crème fraîche</strong> and <strong>drained linguine</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>creamy mushroom & leek linguine</strong></p><p>Tip: Add a splash of starchy pasta water if your sauce is looking a little dry!</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-mushroom-leek-goats-cheese-linguine/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>creamy mushroom & leek linguine</strong> topped with the <strong>crispy meat-free bacon lardons</strong> and <strong>grated cheese</strong></p><p>Season with a good grind of<strong> black pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
